Incoming
Total number of incoming calls.

reportColumnMetadata.name: Queue closed
reportColumnMetadata.description:
Queue closed
Calls that came in when the queue was closed i.e. received a closed queue message.
*Available from version 4.6 SP2 patch 3 - For calls created in earlier version it is logged as an unanswered call.
Included in: Incoming - (Answered, Unanswered, Callbacks requested, Total redirected, Queue closed)

reportColumnMetadata.name: Answered
reportColumnMetadata.description:
Answered
Total number of answered calls.
Included in: Incoming - (Answered, Unanswered, Callbacks requested, Total redirected, Queue closed)

reportColumnMetadata.name: Unanswered
reportColumnMetadata.description:
Unanswered
Total number of abandoned calls. This value does not contain calls that have been redirected.
Included in: Incoming - (Answered, Unanswered, Callbacks requested, Total redirected, Queue closed)

reportColumnMetadata.name: Callbacks requested
reportColumnMetadata.description:
Callbacks requested
Number of calls where the caller has requested a callback. These calls are not included in service levels or queue time values.
*Available from version 5.1 - For calls created in earlier version it is logged as an unanswered call.
Included in: Incoming - (Answered, Unanswered, Callbacks requested, Total redirected, Queue closed)

reportColumnMetadata.name: Callbacks resolved
reportColumnMetadata.description:
Callbacks resolved
Number of callbacks that has been resolved (called back and been answered) These calls are not included in service levels or queue time values.
*Available from version 5.1 - For calls created in earlier version it is logged as an unanswered call.

reportColumnMetadata.name: (Avg) Speed of answer
reportColumnMetadata.description:
(Avg) Speed of answer
The average wait time in queue before being answered.
This duration includes any time spent listeing on promts configured on the queue through a schedule.

reportColumnMetadata.name: (Avg) Call duration
reportColumnMetadata.description:
(Avg) Call duration
The average call duration for answered calls.

reportColumnMetadata.name: Call duration
reportColumnMetadata.description:
Call duration
The total call duration for all answered calls.

reportColumnMetadata.name: (Avg) Queue time unanswered
reportColumnMetadata.description:
(Avg) Queue time unanswered
The average queue time for abandoned calls. This value describes how long callers that have not received any answer have waited in the queue before cancelling the call.

reportColumnMetadata.name: Total redirected
reportColumnMetadata.description:
Total redirected
The total number of calls that have been redirected because of no logged in agents, nightmode or queue overflow.
Included in: Incoming - (Answered, Unanswered, Callbacks requested, Total redirected, Queue closed)

reportColumnMetadata.name: Redirected (no agents/overflow)
reportColumnMetadata.description:
Redirected (no agents/overflow)
Number of calls that have been redirected because no agents were logged in or because of overflow (ex: full queue).

reportColumnMetadata.name: Redirected (queue timeout)
reportColumnMetadata.description: Redirected (queue timeout)

reportColumnMetadata.name: Redirected (nightmode)
reportColumnMetadata.description:
Redirected (nightmode)
Number of calls that have been redirected because the queue was in nightmode.

reportColumnMetadata.name: Answered within 20, 40 seconds
reportColumnMetadata.description:
Answered within t1 seconds
Number of calls that have been answered by the group members and where the answer time did not exceed t1* seconds. This value is only based on calls that have been answered by the members of the group i.e. not calls that have been sent on overflow or nightmode.
*t1 is answer time that is defined by the user as a parameter to the report.

reportColumnMetadata.name: Unanswered within 20, 40 seconds
reportColumnMetadata.description:
Unanswered within t1 seconds
Number of calls that have not received an answer by the members of the group and were ended within the user defined answer time t1*. This value is only based on calls that have been answered by the members of the group i.e. not calls that have been sent on overflow or nightmode.
*t1 is answer time that is defined by the user as a parameter to the report.

reportColumnMetadata.name: (%) Service level (20, 40 seconds)
reportColumnMetadata.description:
Service level (%) (t1)
The service time for this report is based on the user defined (t1) time. Service level is a value in percent that describes how a group have answered their calls. The service level describes the number of calls that have been answered or abandoned within a defined service time divided by the number of incoming calls.
Example: If the service time is set to 20 seconds. If there are a total of 100 incoming calls where 80 are answered and 20 are abandoned, 40 of the incoming calls are answered within the service time (in this case 20 seconds) and 10 of the abandoned calls are abandoned within the service time, the calculation is : Service level = 40 + 10 / 100 which in this case works out at 0.5 or 50%. The result describes the percentage of calls that have been answered or abandoned within the service time and are therefore ok because if the caller disconnects within the service time the abandoned call is logged as an ok abandoned call.

reportColumnMetadata.name: (%) Answered
reportColumnMetadata.description:
(%) Answered
Percentage of all incoming calls that have been answered. (This value does not contain calls that have been redirected and answered in the next step).

reportColumnMetadata.name: (%) Unanswered
reportColumnMetadata.description:
(%) Unanswered
Percentage of all incoming calls that have been abandoned (this value does not contain calls that have been redirected).

reportColumnMetadata.name: (%) Redirected
reportColumnMetadata.description:
(%) Redirected
Percentage of all incoming calls that have been redirected because of no logged in agents, nightmode or queue overflow.
